Panel Starts to Probe Rwanda 's Genocide
ADDIS ABABA , November 18 ( Xinhua ) -- The International Panel of Eminent Personalities to Investigate the 1994 Genocide in Rwanda ( IPEP ) , has now become operational in Addis Ababa .
Churchill Ewumbue-Monono , Administrative and Information Officer of IPEP Secretariat , told Xinhua Wednesday afternoon here that a panel Secretariat has been established and the panel held its first meeting here between October 26 and 28 , 1998 to prepare its program of activities .
Official inauguration will take place in January 1999 in Addis for IPEP , which was set up by the Organization of African Unity ( OAU ) on June 3 , 1998 in Ouagadougou , Burkina Faso .
" Because of the high expectations in Africa and the world at large on the panel 's final report and the need to maintain transparency we have decided to keep the public permanently informed on the panel 's activities , " he said .
The panel , with all its VIP members , appealed for cooperation and support from the OAU member states and the international community in the search for the truth about the Rwanda genocide , the information officer said .
